>Both springs and plungers are stock.  One long spring, one short.  One
grooved plunger, one not grooved. <

I thought the dual relief setup should get two non-grooved plungers.  Only
the single relief should use the grooved plunger.

I cannot remember where I read/heard that from, but I think it is standard
practice.  Maybe better oil pressure?  


